snippet: The possibilities for progress on the issue will be determined in the House of Representatives, where many conservative Republicans are frustrated over their meager gains from the two-week shutdown.
abstract: Pres Obama and other leading Democrats say an immigration overhaul should be back on agenda in Congress, as fiscal crisis subsides; still, possibilities for progress on issue will be determined in the House, where many conservative Republicans are fuming over their meager gains from the two-week shutdown and turning their ire against Obama, saying he failed to negotiate with them.

byline.original: By JULIA PRESTON and ASHLEY PARKER

lead_paragraph: The possibilities for progress on the issue will be determined in the House of Representatives, where many conservative Republicans are frustrated over their meager gains from the two-week shutdown.

headline.main: Democrats Aim to Restore Immigration to Agenda
